### Custom Size

Pass a number to set a custom pixel size.

<Example demo="loader-custom-size-demo">
  <LoaderCustomSizeDemo />
</Example>

## API Reference

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `aria-label` | `string` | `"Loading"` | Accessible label for the status indicator. |
| `size` | `"sm" \| "base" \| "lg" \| number` | `"base"` | Loader size. Numeric values are treated as pixels. |
| `class` | `string` | — | Additional CSS classes. |
| `style` | `string` | — | Additional inline styles. |

Loader also accepts standard SVG attributes except `width` and `height`, which are controlled by the `size` prop.

## Accessibility

The loader renders with `role="status"` and an accessible label. Override `aria-label` when the loading context needs a more specific announcement.
